      "description": "This FD3S chassis represents the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering, maintained in concours-level condition. Power is delivered by a flawlessly balanced 13B-REW rotary engine featuring its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, ensuring a linear torque curve and crisp throttle response. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 5-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The suspension geometry remains true to its lightweight ethos with aluminum double-wishbones at all four corners, providing surgical turn-in. Zero vacuum leaks, perfect compression across all rotor faces, and a pristine undercarriage make this a definitive collector-grade specimen for the serious purist.",
